  "prompt": "My Website is down since 2 Days. What should I do?",
  "response": "If your website is down, here are steps to troubleshoot and resolve the issue:\n\n1. Check Basic Connectivity\n- Verify internet connection\n- Try accessing the website from different devices/networks\n- Use online website status checking tools\n\n2. Contact Web Hosting Provider\n- Call their support team\n- Check their status page for known issues\n- Ask about potential server problems\n- Request detailed error logs\n\n3. Technical Troubleshooting\n- Check DNS settings\n- Verify domain registration is active\n- Review hosting account billing status\n- Examine server error logs\n- Check website files for corruption\n\n4. Potential Causes to Investigate\n- Expired domain\n- Unpaid hosting bill\n- Server hardware failure\n- DDoS attack\n- Coding/configuration errors\n- Malware infection\n\n5. Temporary Mitigation\n- Redirect traffic to a placeholder page\n- Set up email notifications\n- Backup website files\n- Prepare alternative hosting option\n\n6. Professional Help\n- Consult your web developer\n- Hire a technical support specialist\n- Consider managed hosting services\n\n7. Preventive Measures\n- Regular backups\n- Monitoring services\n- Redundant hosting\n- Updated security protocols\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
